reviews.text:
I wanted to really enjoy this but, it could not  deliver. I ordered the lunch special, along with the an order of cheese bread .

The cheese bread was awesome. It was fresh, and had incredible flavor. The cheese bread also comes with marinara dipping sauce.

The main reason I had issues enjoying the food is the pizza. The crust was not crispy but, it was dry enough. I could tell the cheese was also dried out. Maybe if the crust was flavored, it may have been enjoyable somewhat but, this was not the case. I just feel the pizza may have been re-baked one too many times.

I will try them again cause if the cheese bread can taste the way it did, then the pizza can be good too.

I really want to like this place since it is pretty close to my home and there are not many non-chain restaurants to choose from  so, will see in the future.

This was our first time here. The food was awesome. The wings the Margarita pizza all were delicious and the onion rings were 10 out of 10 and the amount they give you is freaking awesome for the price. They do not hold back here. Highly recommend.
I use to go to Josie‚Äôs all the time in Metro-West 15+ years ago, I was so happy to see a location open up closer to me here! The food brought back so many great memories!

Welcome Josie's Pizza. The review: Pizza:
The good -> hot ‚úîÔ∏è fresh ‚úîÔ∏è tasty ‚úîÔ∏è as ordered ‚úîÔ∏è
Now the room for improvement -> dough could be a bit more crisp, we were really looking for no flop.

Jalape√±o poppers (cheddar): very tasty, just right in the cooked to perfection category. *please offer a side of marinara, I think it would have pared really well.

Josie's Brew: very good, more on the light side than medium bodied, however very refreshing and tasty. It was a joy to drink.

Staff: A+ you have a good crew, do what you must to keep them.very professional, kind, and seemed to be enjoying their work.

Price: more than fair, leaning towards reasonable. We felt the price was on target for the area, and definitely a adequate for the food and drinks.

While I am not a huge pizza fan, I really like the pizza here. Granted, I have only eaten here twice in the last month. (And I‚Äôve gotten the same pizza: the rustic mushroom.  Yum!!)
I had the lunch special of salad, garlic bread and a drink and thought the bread was quite good.  Salad was slightly above average. Sweet tea is just right: not too sweet.
Service is good.   I gave the atmosphere a 4 simply because it is so open and not warm and cozy.  But the chairs are comfortable and not just metal.  So that is a plus.

I spent extra money because I wanted pizza for later.  I‚Äôd say their prices are about what lunch would cost for one person at most tip paying restaurants.

detailedReviews.author: Megan Burge
detailedReviews.text: We used to go to the Josie's in Orlando and the wings were always my favorite, so we were excited to have a location in Clermont. It's a casual setting with some bar seats at the counter with a good number of tables for seating. We sat at the bar and ordered a couple beers, a small cheese pizza, and some wings. Everything was really tasty and just like I remembered it from 10+ years ago. The butter garlic Parmesan wings are so good, perfectly crispy without being dry. A lot of cheese pizzas taste the same but theirs just tastes better, good sauce and cheese blend makes a big difference. Service was friendly and the music brought back a lot of nostalgia for me. I'll definitely come back for more wings!

Walking in everything looks nice and clean.

detailedReviews.author: Gerald Williams
detailedReviews.text: My wife and I would frequently go to the Josie‚Äôs Pizza and Wings in Orlando, and  we Loved their food, as well as the service. We Never Had a Problem or complaints. We were super thrilled to see Josie‚Äôs come to Clermont. However, On Friday 03/21/2025 just before closing we placed an order of (20) wings for dinner that we were going to pick up. The wings were (10) hot and (10) bbq the hot wings were saturated in the sauce, So much sauce that the wings were swimming in sauce, the  take out box was full of wing sauce and the wings were just saturated. The bbq sauce was just dumped over the wings, most of the wings on the bottom had no sauce they were not tossed in bbq sauce, just smothered with sauce on top of the wings. We were extremely disappointed, and we felt like we wasted our money. The cook could definitely without a doubt use more training on how to properly prepare the wings. I hope that this review will help and is taken constructively. I hate spending my hard earned money on anything that is inadequate. I will still continue to go to Josie‚Äôs Orlando location ,but sadly it will be a while before I return to the Clermont location. I am hoping that the Clermont location will do better in the future. I generally do not leave reviews, but I felt compelled to share my thoughts and I hope that Josie‚Äôs really does better in the future. And in closing, I now know that I must inspect the food before leaving any establishment

detailedReviews.author: Savannah Ragone
detailedReviews.text:
The owners response speaks for itself in the sense that they couldnt manage to even get my name right when it's directly in front of them, they did not address the inaccurate pricing on their menu which was our largest problem, and despite it sounding like they went back to look at cameras, they got quite a few things wrong. First off, no server checked on us after our order was taken. Someone else may have gotten our napkins, after I called them over because our server was not coming over. Other servers did walk near our table but no one checked on us, they were waiting on other tables. Im the one who asked for the check because no one was coming back- my husband went up to ask why a personal pizza was almost $20 when the menu DOES NOT LIST ANY TOPPINGS AS PREMIUM. Which was my main issue. Funny, the owner doesnt address the price innacuracy at all in their response. We were both sitting on our phones... because we had been finished with our food for quite awhile and no one was coming over with the bill. Were we supposed to just stare at each other until our server noticed we were finished?
Also the fact that you dont know what a pizza oven is... speaks for itself. Google it. I truly meant what I said when I said its something I could make at home, but to be honest? I have and could make a better pizza at home. Piesanos may be similar in price to yours, but the quality is far higher. And the service is insanely better.

I had high hopes for this place and was really let down. Our server essentially ignored us. When I finally went up to ask for our check, the bill was higher than expected. One of our personal pizzas was ringing up as $18.99. I asked about it and they said we got premium toppings. Nowhere on the menu did it say anything about some toppings costing more than others, it just says personal pizzas are $1.50 per topping. Basically I got ripped off and 100% got overcharged. The girl serving us was rude and dismissive as well as being inattentive. Id love to address her by name instead of as "the girl" but she didnt give us a name. As far as the quality of the pizza itself, its maybe a 5/10. It looks like something youd throw together at home. The quality was not there for the prices they charge. If you want good pizza thats actually worth the cost (because this place is WAY overpriced) Piesanos down Citrus Tower has way better service, the pizzas are cooked in an actual pizza oven, and the pricing is transparent. Plus, free bread. Id highly reccomend that establishment over this one if you want pizza thats actually good.

We tried the new Josie‚Äôs in Clermont today. Bruna and Adriano were extremely attentive and friendly. We even saw Florence, the owner and she greeted us as she always does at other locations.

We are regulars at the Metrowest location, and literally being there pretty much once a week, we can attest to the‚Ä¶
1. Extremely high quality food. (Literally my daughter will only eat Josie‚Äôs pizza). We always order wings, which are our favorite!! And the onion rings are also a musthave for an appetizer.
2. Amazingly great choice of music.
3. Atmosphere is always just right. Never too packed and can always TALK, not shout.
4. Lastly, and probably our favorite part about being at Josie‚Äôs, is the amazing staff, especially Alex who has a Josie‚Äôs brew in my husbands hand as we walk in and  knows our order from memory. Salgado is just as amazing, respectful and also knows our order by heart. The rest of staff is great as well. David, the other owner, always makes it a point to stop at our table to ask how our family is doing, talk about baseball, cars, etc‚Ä¶.he has seen our kids grow.

detailedReviews.text:
There are "premium" toppings that aren't listed as such on the menu, so my pizza ended up being more that anticipated. Which wouldn't be a bad thing if the pizza was really good. Despite having 5 toppings on mine, I was only able to recognize 2, maybe 3.

The server came back only one time during the entire time being there.

When asking about the price discrepancy, they informed me of the "premium" toppings, which I informed them is not on the menu. I was just showed a tablet with their pricing.

The breadsticks were probably the best thing there. The water taste bad, which is how Clermont water taste, I would hope they install filters for that.

Can't say I'll be coming back. It was worth least looking into.

I highly recommend visiting Piesanos right down the road. Very well priced with very good quality.

Was excited to try the new pizza place since it said NY style pizza. Was very disappointed when we opened the box and immediately saw it was definitely not NY style pizza. Breadsticks were good. I would try the wings if I went back, but I definitely would not get the pizza again.

Editing my response for the owner reply... I like to give honest reviews, so I gave my honest review of how my family felt about our order. We added this to our Friday night order out and spent around $70, which I feel allows me to give my honest opinion. As someone from the East Coast who is used to a completely different type of NY style pizza (very large fat Neapolitan style with crust you can fold in half), this was not like that so that's how my review was based. I did say the breadsticks were good and I would try the wings. All feedback should be appreciated, not just perfect reviews..

detailedReviews.text: Excellent Pizza, cool atmosphere, super nice and accommodating staff! Highly recommend to check out this place!

detailedReviews.author: Raphael Ninja Turtle
detailedReviews.text:
Came to know the new location after trying Windermere and Metrowest, I was blown away
Everything was served in time and the attention was prompt
Loved the fried ravioli too
Kudos

detailedReviews.author: Joe Duckworth
detailedReviews.text:
Not quite 1/2  supreme, disappointed in that, for $26, come on Josie !!!

Update, shout out to Josies. They are offering me a free " do over" Thanks for reaching out to me. The pizza and service was good, was just disappointed in the 1/2 an 1/2, I should've checked it before driving home.

detailedReviews.author: Valerie Climenhaga
detailedReviews.text: I came in to pick up an order for my job. The pizza was pretty good. The salad I ordered was a bit on the pricey side, but it was still good.

detailedReviews.author: Mike Schmelzle
detailedReviews.text: Wow we had the wings with the citrus chipotle bbq the regular bbq and the garlic Parmesan the garlic Parmesan was my favorite.   We had the garlic bread while waiting the wings and the portion was large. The garlic bread had a nice crispy crust and so soft inside seasoned perfectly.   Service was excellent friendly personable the owner checked on us to make sure we were happy.   Don't hesitate to try Josie's. I ordered the margarita pizza to go I'm sure it will be great üëç

detailedReviews.author: Mimi Rollins
detailedReviews.text: My family has been coming to Josie's since they opened in 1992 in Metrowest!! We love the pizza, wings and beer - it IS SIMPLY THE BEST.  My father (George Boone) found Josie's one day when Domino's was closed in 1992. They were still a small take out only at that time. The pizza was so good, delicious and wholesome - definitely NOT Domino's!! My husband and I moved to Lockhart and drove back to Metrowest just to get Josie's (since moved to Lake County). One day driving down 27 I saw a familiar sign and my excitement was off the charts. No more chain pizza.  Thank you Josie's for coming to Clermont. People you must, if you haven't already, take your behind to Josie's and tell them the Boone family sent you.

detailedReviews.author: Ruthy Delvillar
detailedReviews.text: I love these pizzas. This time we ordered my favorite, the one with ham and pineapple. I ate it super fast and forgot to take a picture üòÇüòÇ and another one with sweetie peppers, pepperoni, basil, both super delicious, it's a contrast of flavors. If you like crispy, thin pizzas with a special sauce, you have to come and try them. We were served by 2 super friendly girls, Valery and Katy. I recommend this place 100% üíú

detailedReviews.author: Kurt Breitfeller
detailedReviews.text:
As a ‚Äòtransplanted‚Äô New Yorker from Long Island, I must say the pizza and calzone were pretty good. Service was quick and professional yet friendly and personable. We ate from the lunch menu, which made the price very affordable. The artichoke and spinach calzone was better than the plain cheese pizza, although the pizza sauce was fresh and authentic.

The one drawback noted was the thickness of the crust. While still foldable, the crust was floppy, soggy and very thin. This may just be a preference thing, but a large slice should remain foldable and firm.

Will definitely be going back for a quick bite at anytime. Well done!

detailedReviews.author: Chris Carcano
detailedReviews.text: Second time visiting and it gets better and better. David is such a great owner. He made us feel especially our kids feel so welcomed. Food was amazing! This is our new regular spot!

detailedReviews.author: Marcal Cohen
detailedReviews.text: Ordered pizza and wings to go. Everything was delicious! Service was great. Employees were quick, helpful, and even offered me water while I waited. I'm not understanding the bad reviews. This is now our new favorite pizza place.

detailedReviews.author: Ed
detailedReviews.text: Great Place! Great Food! The service was excellent. Bruna was a rockstar! Knocked it out of the park. Glad they‚Äôre now in Clermont.

detailedReviews.author: Chase Hansen
detailedReviews.text:
We stopped by Josie‚Äôs Pizza & Wings in Clermont for lunch, and it was a great experience! We ordered two personal pizzas and drinks, and the value was excellent. The pizzas were delicious, perfectly portioned, and made fresh.

The service was quick and friendly, so we could enjoy our meal without a long wait. We left feeling satisfied and happy to have found a new go-to pizza spot. Highly recommend Josie‚Äôs if you‚Äôre looking for quality pizza and great service in Clermont!

detailedReviews.author: Hector Ilarraza
detailedReviews.text:
This place is amazing. Great food. Great customer service.  The food is fresh. The owner was very friendly as well. You need to try this place.  So far, I had the wings, the Italian sub, the chicken palm.  You will not go wrong. Good prices as and food.

Thanks, Taber, Florence, and Griffin!!!!

detailedReviews.author: Skylar Kate
detailedReviews.text: Alex was really nice and I had a great experience here and the food is really good. I will definitely be coming back!

detailedReviews.author: Joan Marie
detailedReviews.text: 0 complain at all food was great and service amazing even the owner talk to us they're very attentive food came quickly and fresh we got lunch specials and the prices was just right and the freshness of the food was great for the 1st time here definitely come back soon.. The place is super clean as well..I personally order the personal calzone full of meat, cheese and cook to perfection..

detailedReviews.author: Jonathan Georggi
detailedReviews.text: Pizza is THE BEST in town, the owners are wonderful, and they have such an amazing beer selection on tap. Inside is super nice as well and is very very welcoming. I‚Äôm so glad Josie‚Äôs pizza came to clermont! üòÄ

detailedReviews.author: Ronnie Kravitz CDE
detailedReviews.text: My new fave pizza spot in clermont. My pizza, fries, tenders and wings were great and I can be a very picky person

detailedReviews.author: Christopher Johnson
detailedReviews.text:
Welcome Josie's Pizza. The review: Pizza:
The good -> hot ‚úîÔ∏è fresh ‚úîÔ∏è tasty ‚úîÔ∏è as ordered ‚úîÔ∏è
Now the room for improvement -> dough could be a bit more crisp, we were really looking for no flop.

Jalape√±o poppers (cheddar): very tasty, just right in the cooked to perfection category. *please offer a side of marinara, I think it would have pared really well.

Josie's Brew: very good, more on the light side than medium bodied, however very refreshing and tasty. It was a joy to drink.

Staff: A+ you have a good crew, do what you must to keep them.very professional, kind, and seemed to be enjoying their work.

Price: more than fair, leaning towards reasonable. We felt the price was on target for the area, and definitely a adequate for the food and drinks.

detailedReviews.author: Aaron Stratton
detailedReviews.text: We walked in at 12:30pm on Saturday and sat at the bar. Dining room was pretty full with no food on any tables, which makes me think everyone came in at once‚Ä¶ maybe?  We sat for 5 minutes before being acknowledged and were told we would be helped shortly. Several minutes went by before being given menus. We walked out at 12:45 without anybody ever saying anything else. Noticed there were no prices on menus for anything, which seemed odd. Maybe we‚Äôll try again in a couple of months? I‚Äôve been to other locations and was pleased‚Ä¶ was happy this location was coming, initially.  Not sure now. Also‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm giving two stars instead of one because I had a good experience at the two other locations I have visited.

detailedReviews.author: Marly Gregoire
detailedReviews.text:
I will definitely be back. The breadsticks were so freaking good. The wings were yummy and crunchy (hate soggy wings). And the pizza was good (although I was a bit surprised by the price of toppings). My kid is super picky and he ate! The waitresses gave him all the attention and love and I think that made the difference. The whole staff was so helpful. I think we were asked if we had everything we need like 20 times. They‚Äôre off to a great start. I think I‚Äôll order it again tonight.

We went on a Friday night around 7:30pm.

detailedReviews.author: Lucy Schnallinger
detailedReviews.text: Fourth time back and food is awesome! Best wings in Clermont. The Italian combo always delicious. Wings are spot on! We get wet, hot garlic. Amazing. Servers are so nice.

detailedReviews.author: Diane L. Rogers PA
detailedReviews.text:
Not good!!
I wanted to go because I used to get Josie‚Äôs wings when I worked in Metrowest.  So the 3 of us went because of that reason only. No prices on the menu when we got there- so took awhile for waitress to bring over the one machine that had prices.  We got teriyaki wings, a calzone and a meatball sub and fries,2 drinks & a beer.  Now out of 4 items- the only good on was the fries. Hot and crispy. The wings were no where near crispy- the skin was chewy- worse wings I have ever had. I wanted to turn them back but the other 2 said it would take forever so I just ate 2 (took the skin off)and took rest home to air fry. No one asked me if I wanted them chewy, crispy or extra crispy- never mentioned it. ( per another review) The calzone was over cooked , almost burnt looking in top and the meatball sub was also overheated and dry. Meatballs were way over cooked. I do t know if pizza oven was too hot or what. I don‚Äôt think meatballs were made in house( didn‚Äôt taste like it)
We eat out a lot as usually just 2 of us .
Obviously we will not be going back again.

detailedReviews.author: Shelly Luff
detailedReviews.text: We missed Josie's when we moved from Orlando to Lake County. Best wings ever! So glad they finally opened a location in Clermont!

positive.author: Jennifer
positive.text:
While I am not a huge pizza fan, I really like the pizza here. Granted, I have only eaten here twice in the last month. (And I‚Äôve gotten the same pizza: the rustic mushroom.  Yum!!)
I had the lunch special of salad, garlic bread and a drink and thought the bread was quite good.  Salad was slightly above average. Sweet tea is just right: not too sweet.
Service is good.   I gave the atmosphere a 4 simply because it is so open and not warm and cozy.  But the chairs are comfortable and not just metal.  So that is a plus.

I spent extra money because I wanted pizza for later.  I‚Äôd say their prices are about what lunch would cost for one person at most tip paying restaurants.

positive.author: Jason Maynard
positive.text: Excellent Service today from Valeria! She had several customers and made sure she was attentive to everyone at the same time. Food was excellent too! We will definitely be back soon.

neutral.author: Brandon Bil
neutral.text:
I wanted to really enjoy this but, it could not  deliver. I ordered the lunch special, along with the an order of cheese bread .

The cheese bread was awesome. It was fresh, and had incredible flavor. The cheese bread also comes with marinara dipping sauce.

The main reason I had issues enjoying the food is the pizza. The crust was not crispy but, it was dry enough. I could tell the cheese was also dried out. Maybe if the crust was flavored, it may have been enjoyable somewhat but, this was not the case. I just feel the pizza may have been re-baked one too many times.

I will try them again cause if the cheese bread can taste the way it did, then the pizza can be good too.

I really want to like this place since it is pretty close to my home and there are not many non-chain restaurants to choose from  so, will see in the future.

neutral.author: Z Z
neutral.text: Food was ok. I've tasted better pizza. Service was fairly slow but it was crowded. Atmosphere was that of a take out place.

neutral.author: Linda Goncher
neutral.text:
I wanted to see if the hype was true. We only tried the pizza which was just ok. Needed to be more well done and seriously Piesano‚Äôs gives you more bang flavor wise for the price of their pizza. Josie‚Äôs is a big high on the price of their pies and extremely overpriced on the large Caesar‚Äôs salad. When we mentioned the portion size for two at $10 was small the manager said ‚Äúwell, normally it‚Äôs a bit bigger‚Äù. REALLY, that‚Äôs what you say to your customers?? She proactively took it back but maybe added 2 Tablespoons of romaine to the salad. B

Manager tried to make everything right but we could tell they were happy to get rid of us seniors. I assumed they knew we would never be back so wrote us off. In the restaurant industry that‚Äôs a mistake as we live in a large senior community. The other servers were ok but seemed poorly trained.. No atmosphere. You could use a few cheery pictures on the wall. Very plain tables spaced apart.

In summary, this chain isn‚Äôt seeking out  the senior population but will probably be fine with the younger population of commuters as Swigs is around the corner

negative.author: Martina Allen
negative.text:
Hands down, worst tasting Pizza I‚Äôve ever had. How do you make Pizza taste bad?
I had a calzone and had mouthfuls of just ricotta cheese. I tasted nothing else. It was gross. Ratio is important. My kid had a cheese pizza and didn‚Äôt even eat half. It tasted bad. For what they charge it was definitely a fail. Marcos and papa John‚Äôs have better tasting food. Too bad. I was hopeful.

negative.author: Emmanuel Nieves
negative.text:
Walking in everything looks nice and clean.
First time going, told the lady it's our first time going. No advice or recommendations from the menu?
It was not busy at all when we came in.
I asked for a 12inch chicken Caesar Sub with fries, my wife asked for a ceaser salad.

Receipt came in. They just wanted to mark the difference off the total instead of actually correcting it online.

Online price for a 6" chicken Caesar sub is 7.99$
Not sure why yall charge 8.99

negative.author: C E
negative.text: As an Italian from  New York who knows what REAL NY pizza should be, this isn't it.  Much better choices in the area.  One look and one bite will tell you to go elsewhere.  I hope this review works better for the owner since the last one wasn't detailed enough.  Instead of telling people to kick rocks, maybe you should use the feedback to improve.  Pretty good sign that management doesn't really care about quality when they can't handle criticism.
